
@startuml
skinparam linetype zigzag

class Person {
  -personID: String
  -name: String
  -phoneNumber: String
  -keywords: List<String>
  -institutionCode: String
}

class Institution {
  -institutionCode: String
  -name: String
}

class Article {
  -doi: String
  -title: String
  -authors: List<Person>
  -authorPositions: List<Integer>
}

class PeerReviewedPaper {
  -citationCount: Integer
  -reviewers: List<Person>
}

class TechnicalReport {
  -publishingInstitutionCode: String
}

class Publisher {
  -name: String
}

class Journal {
  -publisherName: String
  -journalName: String
  -impactFactor: Double
}

class Subscription {
  -institutionCode: String
  -journalName: String
  -publisherName: String
}

' Associations
Person "1" *-- "0..*" Article : author of
Person "1" *-- "0..*" Article : reviewer of

Article <|-- PeerReviewedPaper
Article <|-- TechnicalReport

PeerReviewedPaper o-- "0..*" Person : reviewed by

Institution "1" *-- "0..*" TechnicalReport : publishes

Publisher "1" *-- "0..*" Journal : owns

Journal "1" *-- "0..*" Subscription : subscribed to by
Institution "1" *-- "0..*" Subscription : subscribes to

Person "1" -- "1" Institution : works at
@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`Person`** has a unique `personID`, is affiliated with an `Institution`, and can be both an **author** and **reviewer** of articles.
- **`Institution`** is uniquely identified by `institutionCode` and can publish **TechnicalReports** and have **Subscriptions** to **Journals**.
- **`Article`** is the base class for both **PeerReviewedPaper** and **TechnicalReport**. Each article has a unique **DOI**, title, and list of authors (with positions).
- **`PeerReviewedPaper`** includes citation count and reviewers.
- **`TechnicalReport`** must be published by an institution.
- **`Publisher`** can have multiple **Journals** with the same name as other publishers.
- **`Journal`** has an **impact factor** and is associated with a **Subscription** that links institutions to journals.

